# Logging

Human reference: `docs/logging.md`. When adding or changing logs, follow level semantics first, then Dhara conventions below.

## Standard level hierarchy

Severity decreases top → bottom; verbosity increases. **Configured level captures that level and everything more severe** (`logged >= threshold`).

```
FATAL/CRITICAL  — unrecoverable; process must stop
ERROR           — operation failed; app continues
WARN            — unusual but non-blocking; investigate later
INFO            — healthy milestones operators rely on in production
DEBUG           — engineer diagnostics; usually off in production
TRACE           — line-by-line / per-item detail; highest volume
```

| Pick this level when… | Example                                                  |
| --------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------- |
| ERROR                 | Module/command aborts; user-visible failure              | `defs.build-trid-xml failed — archive tool missing`   |
| WARN                  | Completed with caveats                                   | skipped step, verification mismatch                   |
| INFO                  | One sentence a reader needs without DEBUG                | session open/close, phase **finish**, aggregate stats |
| DEBUG                 | Supports troubleshooting; safe to omit from default runs | phase **start**, paths, flags, per-item trace         |
| TRACE                 | Only if `--trace` / explicit verbose mode                | per-definition reduce outcomes                        |

Do **not** emit DEBUG/TRACE content at INFO. Do **not** use INFO for progress counters when a phase-finish line or `--trace` detail is the right tier.

## Rust / tracing (`dhara_tool`)

Use `tracing` macros with explicit targets. Audit/operator events: `target: "dhara_tool::audit"`.

`log` crate severity (lower number = more severe): Error=1, Warn=2, Info=3, Debug=4, Trace=5.  
`tracing-subscriber` filters the same way: setting max level INFO shows INFO+WARN+ERROR, not DEBUG.

Console vs file thresholds (numeric `log` scale: Info=3, Warn=2, Debug=4):

| Flag             | Console  | File      |
| ---------------- | -------- | --------- |
| default          | 3 (INFO) | 3 (INFO)  |
| `--min` / `-m`   | 3 (INFO) | 2 (WARN)  |
| `--trace` / `-t` | 3 (INFO) | 4 (DEBUG) |

Console stays INFO until the new TUI policy lands.

## Dhara operator logs — requirements

Logs are for **humans and agents**, not aggregators. Write plain sentences, one fact per line.

### Tiering (TrID and long modules)

| Category    | INFO                                                 | DEBUG                                        |
| ----------- | ---------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------- |
| Performance | `phase {name} finished in {duration} — {summary}`    | `phase {name} started`                       |
| Reports     | `TrID transform — …` once; module finish summary     | per-definition reduce trace (`--trace` only) |
| Environment | session `mode`, `workers`; module `started — {args}` | flags, log path, resolved paths              |

### Must do

- Single audit dispatch path per progress event (no duplicate callbacks).
- Session INFO: `dhara_tool {version} started — mode=…, workers=…` — **no log path on INFO**.
- Long modules: begin INFO → phase finish INFO lines → aggregate stats once → finish INFO with duration.
- Fast modules: config at DEBUG; one INFO finish line.
- Reduce stage: **no** `(N/total) reduce in progress` milestones at any level.
- `--trace` reduce lines: `({current}/{total}) {file_type} — accepted|rejected: …` with structured suffixes; stats once via `TrID transform —`.
- Parse stage: never log every input file at INFO; phase finish with count/duration only.
- Console progress (direct + TTY): throttled `parse:` / `reduce:` counters on stderr only.

### Must not

- Duplicate the same stage line from runner and caller.
- Dump cumulative counters on every trace line.
- Put self-referential noise on INFO (log file path, “logging initialized”).
- Log field soup / JSON blobs where one sentence suffices.

### When diagnosing

Read `tooling/logs/{date}_dhara_tool*.log` → `started` → `{module} started/finished` → `phase ` / `TrID transform` → `exiting`.
